<TITLE> Polio vaccination takes off </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 8 (bdnews24.com) - Tens of thousands of health workers fanned out across the country Saturday to vaccinate some 24 million children under five against polio, which made a comeback in 2006 after years of absence. The campaign is part of the government's continuous efforts to eradicate polio from the country after some new cases were found in 2006, the health ministry said. Health adviser ASM Matiur Rahman moved to a vaccination camp in the city's Mohammadpur area to officially start the day's campaign. The health workers set up many makeshift camps at bus and railway stations in the capital and elsewhere to immunise the children. bd
